{
  "texts": [
    "This customer likely knows the watch's MSRP as well as further offer prices across different online sales platforms.",
    "Hence, the customer obtains a benchmark price for all watches in his choice set and the likelihood that he is willing to overpay this benchmark price is way lower than the likelihood that he is willing to underpay his benchmark price, suggesting a negatively skewed willingness to pay distribution.",
    "• Markov chain choice (MCC): The Markov chain choice model proposed by Blanchet et al. (2016) can approximate any discrete choice model within the RUM framework under mild assumptions (see Blanchet et al. 2016).",
    "The model represents the customer choice process by a Markov chain where each state corresponds to a product or the no-purchase option.",
    "Every product state is connected with state 0 representing the no-purchase option."
  ]
}